# Important Kafka Concept: Acknowledgements

Currently we are using Kafka defaults.

In production you'll often see:

```python
acks='all'
```

Why?

Because Kafka supports different delivery guarantees.

---

## acks=0

```text id="s3ms9v"
Send and forget
```

Fastest.

Risky.

---

## acks=1

```text id="t1eq6u"
Leader confirms write
```

Balanced.

---

## acks=all

```text id="f4u7ko"
All replicas confirm write
```

Safest.

Slightly slower.

---

# Interview Question

### What does acks=all mean?

Strong Answer:

> The producer waits until all in-sync replicas acknowledge the write before considering the message successfully written, providing the strongest durability guarantee.

